Pre-Game Insights: Marcus Semien, coming off a one-hit showing in his last game (1-for-5), will take the field for the Texas Rangers versus Bryan Woo and the Seattle Mariners on Sunday.
Semien is hitting .232 with 26 doubles, two triples, 22 home runs and 59 walks.
Semien ranks 49th in homers and 54th in RBI in baseball.
Semien is 4-for-6 with a double and a home run over his career versus Bryan Woo.
Against Bryan Woo last year, Semien went 4-for-6 with a double and a home run.
Bryan Woo (8-3 with a 2.85 ERA and 89 strikeouts in 110 1/3 innings pitched) gets the nod for the Mariners in his 21st start of the season.
Woo is looking to put up his 11th quality start of the year.
